        "text": "Light troops trained in the noble art of throwing things and running away. Skirmishers excel at harassing enemies, avoiding death, and reminding heavier soldiers why mobility matters. Historians call them “hit-and-run specialists.” The enemy just calls them cowards — usually right before getting another javelin in the face."
      }
    ]
